value.value: Adult intrinsic neuron with ipsilateral arbors in a single VNC neuromere (Takemura et al., 2023; Marin et al., 2024). It is a secondary neuron of the 17A hemilineage (Takemura et al., 2023; Marin et al., 2024). It receives input in the leg neuropil and sends output to the leg neuropil (Takemura et al., 2023; Marin et al., 2024). Its predicted neurotransmitter is acetylcholine (Eckstein et al., 2024). There are approximately 6 of these cells per organism and their somas are found in the mesothoracic neuromere, metathoracic neuromere and prothoracic neuromere (Takemura et al., 2023; Marin et al., 2024).

It receives input in the upper tectulum and sends output to the upper tectulum (Takemura et al., 2023; Marin et al., 2024). Its predicted neurotransmitter is acetylcholine (Eckstein et al., 2024). There are approximately 2 of these cells per organism and their somas are found in the mesothoracic neuromere (Takemura et al., 2023; Marin et al., 2024).
